<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Cost Factors</p>
    <h2>What affects freezer repair cost in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="factors-grid">
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128295;</div><h3>Type of failure</h3><p>A defrost heater is a straightforward swap. A compressor replacement involves refrigerant evacuation, new component installation, and system recharge &mdash; significantly more time and labor.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127991;</div><h3>Freezer type</h3><p>Chest freezers, upright freezers, and drawer freezers each have different configurations that affect labor time. Built-in models require more access work and are at the higher end of labor ranges.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127777;</div><h3>LA climate impact</h3><p>The Inland Empire (Rancho Cucamonga, Ontario) sees summer temps above 105&deg;F &mdash; compressors run at maximum capacity for months. Freezers in these areas show wear faster and defrost systems fail more frequently.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128197;</div><h3>Age of the unit</h3><p>Parts availability drops for units over 12&ndash;15 years old. Older compressors are often more expensive to source. We tell you the parts situation before you approve the repair.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127959;</div><h3>Built-in vs. freestanding</h3><p>Built-in and under-counter freezers require removing cabinetry panels and working in tight clearances. This adds labor time compared to a freestanding unit with full access.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128721;</div><h3>Root cause diagnosis</h3><p>A defrost system failure that&rsquo;s been running unchecked leads to ice buildup that stresses the compressor. We diagnose and fix the root cause, not just the symptom &mdash; which is visible in the separate labor and parts breakdown.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Repair vs. Replace</p>
    <h2>When to repair a freezer, when to replace it</h2>
    <p class="lead">We give you an honest assessment after diagnosis. Here&rsquo;s the framework we use.</p>
    <div class="rvr-grid">
      <div class="rvr-card repair">
        <h3>Repair makes sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Unit is under 10 years old</li>
          <li>Total repair (labor + parts) is under 50% of replacement value</li>
          <li>It&rsquo;s a built-in or luxury unit &mdash; replacement is disruptive</li>
          <li>Single component failure, not systemic breakdown</li>
          <li>Sealed refrigerant system is intact</li>
