    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does freezer repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor typically runs $200&ndash;$440 for standard brands depending on the repair type. Parts are quoted separately after diagnosis. The $89 diagnostic fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work. Sub-Zero and luxury brands run $320&ndash;$910+ in labor.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why do you quote labor and parts separately?</div><div class="faq-a">Many LA repair companies use flat-rate BlueBook pricing that bundles labor and parts into a single number before diagnosis. We quote them separately so you see exactly what you&rsquo;re paying for. A clogged drain with no part needed and a compressor replacement are completely different jobs &mdash; they shouldn&rsquo;t cost the same.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are parts included in the quoted labor price?</div><div class="faq-a">No &mdash; the prices on this page are labor only. After diagnosis we quote the specific part needed as a separate line item. You see both numbers before approving anything. OEM parts used wherever available.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is freezer repair worth it vs. replacing it?</div><div class="faq-a">For units under 10 years old, repair almost always makes economic sense. A chest freezer or upright freezer is a lot cheaper to repair than to replace and restock. We give you the honest repair-vs-replace math after diagnosis.</div></div>
